1 Introduction

We used the results of the differential expression analysis between untreated samples of EBV vs NOKS cell lines to determine pathways in the KEGG and GO databases using allez. For this analysis, we had to remove the following genes:

In total, we are performing the pathway analysis with 16051 genes.

2 Pathway analysis with Allez

The general idea of this method, is that the pathway database is described by the \(P\times W\) previously known incidence matrix: \[I=(I_{pw}) = \begin{cases} 1,& p\in w\\0&\text{otherwise}\end{cases}\]

And we model a vector of measurements across different samples, or summary statistics \(x = \{ x_p\}\), in our case this is the signal to noise measurement calculated for each gene. The main assumption is the activation hypthesis:

A set of parts is active if and only if all the parts in the set are active

In the paper that I read (Newton et al, 2012) the model used is:

\[ \begin{align} Z_w &\sim \mbox{Ber}(\pi) \\ X_p\vert Z_w = z_w &\sim \mbox{Ber}\left( \alpha + (\beta - \alpha )\max_{w:p\in w} z_w \right) \end{align} \]

This is the discrete version of the model, but we are going to use the continuous version based in the log2FC between EBV and NOKS samples (i.e.the same results from Fig 2). This method cant use MolSigDB, which is the database that is used by GSEA, but the ones with used GO and KEGG are parts of it.

We filtered the genes by selecting the ones with \(\mbox{pvalue} \leq 0.1\), and then divided the genes in three sets:

  • All genes

  • EBV upregulated genes

  • EBV downregulated genes

The default parameter to calculate filter the results is to use a z-score of \(z_* = 5\), since we observed very few differentially expressed genes in this contrast, I used a very conservative threshold \(z_*=1.64\)

2.1 Allez analysis with the GO database:

allez_go = allez(gene_scores, "org.Hs.eg", idtype = "SYMBOL", 
                 library.loc = NULL,
                 sets = "GO", locallist = NULL,
                 universe = "global",
                 transform = c("none"), 
                 annotate = TRUE)

2.2 Allez analysis with the KEGG database:

allez_kegg = allez(gene_scores, "org.Hs.eg", idtype = "SYMBOL", 
                 library.loc = NULL,
                 sets = "KEGG", locallist = NULL,
                 universe = "global",
                 transform = c("none"), 
                 annotate = TRUE)
